      "message": "Line 80: scheduleBackgroundDeactivation() is public and is called from FirebaseMessagingService\u0027s coroutine, but it mutates Handler callback state directly instead of marshalling to the main looper like notePushReceived() does. Handler operations are generally thread-safe, but this makes ordering with lifecycle callbacks and notePushReceived() dependent on cross-thread enqueue timing; a stale service finally block can cancel a more specific grace delay posted from the main thread. Make this method always execute its remove/post sequence on the main handler thread.\n```suggestion\nfun scheduleBackgroundDeactivation(delayMs: Long \u003d BACKGROUND_DEACTIVATION_DELAY_MS) {\n    backgroundHandler.post {\n        backgroundHandler.removeCallbacks(deactivateRunnable)\n        backgroundHandler.postDelayed(deactivateRunnable, delayMs)\n    }\n}\n```",
