      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 83: Background pushes now call restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground() regardless of whether push notifications are currently enabled or a valid push token exists. If the user disables push notifications while the app is backgrounded, a later/stale FCM delivery can reactivate accounts that were intentionally deactivated for background battery saving, and the follow-up deactivation runnable will no-op because enablePushNotifications is false. Gate the restore/reconnect path with the same push-availability condition used by the deactivation runnable.\n```suggestion\nif (!appInForeground \u0026\u0026 app?.mPreferencesService?.settings?.enablePushNotifications \u003d\u003d true \u0026\u0026 app.pushToken !\u003d null) {\n    val isCallPush \u003d isCallNotification || isDhtProxyCallWakeup(remoteMessage)\n    app.notePushReceived(isCallPush)\n    app.mAccountService.restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground()\n    if (isCallPush \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.originalPriority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH) {\n        app.hardwareService.connectivityChanged(true)\n    }\n}\n```",
